---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is my money safe? Who controls my funds?",
    a: "Your funds stay in your wallet positions on Aave and Morpho — the agent never holds them. The backend agent wallet can only call YieldOptimizerCore to supply or withdraw on your behalf. You can pause or kill the agent from the dashboard at any time.",
  },
  {
    q: "What happens if the AI makes a bad decision?",
    a: "Every LLM output is schema-validated before any on-chain call. AgentPolicy enforces daily USD limits, an asset allowlist, and a risk tier cap on-chain. If the LLM response is malformed, the system falls back to a safe mock decision and logs the error — no transaction is sent.",
  },
  {
    q: "Which assets and protocols are supported?",
    a: "Currently USDC and WETH on Aave V3 (mock) and Morpho Blue on Base Sepolia testnet. The mock stack uses MockUSDC and MockAavePool so you can test the full flow without real funds.",
  },
  {
    q: "How does the 24/7 automation actually work?",
    a: "Two independent paths: Chainlink Automation calls performUpkeep() on AutoYieldConsumer.sol every 6 hours, which emits an event the backend listens to. Separately, a node-cron job runs on the Railway backend every 6 hours as a fallback. Both paths call the same LLM and executeManual flow.",
  },
  {
    q: "How do I get test USDC to try it?",
    a: "Click the 'Get 1000 test USDC' button in the Deposit card on the dashboard. The backend mints MockUSDC directly to your wallet address on Base Sepolia — no faucet website needed.",
  },
  {
    q: "What AI model powers the decisions?",
    a: "Qwen 3 235B A22B — a 235-billion parameter Mixture-of-Experts model from Alibaba, accessed via DashScope Singapore. It receives live pool data (APYs, TVL, utilization) and your instruction, then returns a structured JSON decision with protocol, action, amount, risk score, and reasoning.",
  },
  {
    q: "Is this production-ready?",
    a: "This is a hackathon MVP on Base Sepolia testnet. The mock stack (MockUSDC, MockAavePool) simulates real Aave behavior. Smart contract audit and mainnet deployment are planned before any real-fund usage.",
  },
];
---

<section id="faq" class="lp-section lp-divider border-t min-h-screen flex flex-col justify-center px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 sm:py-20">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto w-full">

    <div class="text-center mb-10 sm:mb-12">
      <p class="lp-muted text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="lp-text font-black" style="font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);">
        Common Questions
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 sm:gap-3">
      {faqs.map((faq) => (
        <details class="lp-card group overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between px-5 sm:px-6 py-4 sm:py-5 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
            <span class="lp-text font-medium text-sm pr-4">{faq.q}</span>
            <svg
              class="shrink-0 w-4 h-4 lp-muted transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-45"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M5 12h14"/><path d="M12 5v14"/>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-5 sm:px-6 pb-4 sm:pb-5">
            <p class="lp-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">{faq.a}</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
